"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927716","Home Office","false","2018-06-26","<p>The Home Office records and publishes data, broken down by nationality, of all those who make an asylum claim or are referred to the National Referral mechanism (NRM) as a potential victim of trafficking or modern slavery. Information concerning a claimants route of travel to the United Kingdom is not recorded centrally in a readily accessible format, and could only be provided at disproportionate costs by examination of individual interview transcripts and case files. There are no plans to record this information.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-26T11:45:25.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927716/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927716/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927716/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Human Trafficking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 27 February 2018 to Question 129315, if he will develop a cost-effective means of recording in a readily accessible format the route of travel of people who have been illegally trafficked to the UK.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","155941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927717","Home Office","false","2018-06-27","<p>When the Department receives a request for access to personal data, the data will be provided except where to do so would be likely to prejudice effective immigration control.</p><p>The Department will handle any request for access to personal data held by the Home Office on its merits.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-27T13:26:26.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927717/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927717/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927717/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the immigration exemption in forthcoming data protection legislation, if he will make it his policy that no information relating to the case of a member of the Windrush generation, their children or someone who arrived in the UK between 1973 and 1988 will be withheld from that person if they request their personal data.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","155942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927718","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-28","<p>​Foreign Office officials were in contact with Mr Ramadan Abedi during his detention in May 2017 to provide basic consular assistance. They have been in contact on consular matters since then.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-28T15:03:18.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927718/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927718/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927718/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-20","Ramadan Abedi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 3 April 2018 to Question 133856, on armed conflict: Libya, what communications the Government has had with Ramadan Abedi.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","155905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927719","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-28","<p>As at 25 June 2018, the total number of alleged instances of breaches or violations of International Humanitarian Law (IHL) in Yemen listed on the &quot;Tracker&quot; database maintained by the Ministry of Defence (MOD) is 356. Of these, 14 are duplicate entries, which means that some incidents will have been recorded on more than one occasion likely because of the incomplete nature of Non-Governmental Organisation and media reporting upon which the MOD relies to update the &quot;Tracker&quot;. Dis-aggregating this information to the last 12 months would be misleading without the addition of sensitive contextual information, which I am withholding as its disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice relations between the United Kingdom and other States.</p><p>The MOD does not investigate allegations of IHL violations. The Saudi-led Coalition is best placed to do this, and does so through its Joint Incident Assessment Team.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-06-28T14:48:41.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927719/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927719/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927719/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-20","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many allegations of violations of international humanitarian law in Yemen by the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia his Department has received in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","155906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927720","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-25","<p>​Payments for medical supplies are not subject to US sanctions. Whether to engage in transactions with Iran, including in sectors exempted from US sanctions – such as medical supplies – remains a commercial decision for individual banks. However, this Government encourages legitimate trade with Iran and continues to engage US and European counterparts to help facilitate this.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-25T16:55:37.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927720/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927720/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927720/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-20","Iran: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 21 May 2018 to Question 146957, and given that payment for medicines is not exempt from US sanctions, how UK entities will be able to sell medicine into Iran when payment cannot be made from Iranian to UK banks.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","155907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927721","Treasury","false","2018-06-25","<p>The Future of Child Benefit Programme will migrate current Child Benefit customer data from the existing DWP IT System across to a more modern, stable and flexible IT system within HMRC. The Programme is currently on track for delivery in late 2019.</p><p>It will enable HMRC to maintain existing claims and payments, and process new claims for Child Benefit within the HMRC IT estate.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-06-25T13:38:45.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927721/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927721/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927721/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-20","Child Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of progress on delivering the future of child benefit transformation project, and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","155822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927722","Treasury","false","2018-06-25","<p>The childcare service is working well, following HMRC’s improvements. This is demonstrated by over 80% parent satisfaction with the service since the start of the year. As with all new digital services, HMRC are continuing to improve the customer journey in response to customer feedback.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-06-25T16:45:29.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927722/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927722/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927722/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-20","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of progress on delivering the tax-free childcare new front end project; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","155823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927723","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-25","<p>United Kingdom Security Vetting (UKSV) has an obligation to act in accordance with Data Protection legislation.</p><p>UKSV was created on 1 January 2017, since this date there have been five applications for data to be shared with police authorities, all requests have been responded to in accordance with Data Protection Legislation.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-06-25T16:22:58.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927723/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927723/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927723/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-20","United Kingdom Security Vetting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what requirement the UK Security Vetting Agency has to hand over vetting material to the police; how many such applications have been received by that agency; and how many such applications have been complied with by that agency in the last two years.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","155681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927724","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-29","<p>The Joint Maritime Commission’s Subcommittee on Wages of Seafarers is a bipartite meeting between representatives of the seafarers and the shipowners. Government representatives do not normally attend or take part and the composition of the sub-Committee should not be influenced by Governments.</p><p>The participants who attend are a matter only for the seafarers and the shipowners groups respectively and those who attend the sub-Committee will be recognised as being representative of their sector by the social partners and the ILO.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-06-29T10:46:20.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927724/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927724/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927724/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-20","Shipping: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment she has made of the validity of the negotiating position of seafarer representatives ahead of the meeting of the Joint Maritime Commission's Subcommittee on Wages of Seafarers at the International Labour Organisation in Geneva on 20 to 21 June 2018.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","155776"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927725","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-29","<p>Network Rail’s commercial estate in England and Wales comprises over 3,000 business tenants. Network Rail does not hold figures for the number of people employed by its tenants.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-29T09:20:32.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927725/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927725/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927725/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-20","Network Rail: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the number of people employed in businesses directly affected by Network Rail's decision to sell its commercial assets.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","155877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927726","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-29","<p>The training of drivers on new or upgraded routes is a matter for the operator and may be undertaken by a variety of training methods.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-29T10:18:12.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927726/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927726/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927726/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-20","Govia Thameslink Railway: Timetables","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with Govia Thameslink Railway on whether all sections of new routes implemented as part of the new rail timetable must be covered in a classroom setting before a driver covers the route.","true","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","155766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927727","Home Office","false","2018-06-25","<p>Applications for Indefinite Leave to Remain and other forms of leave to remain are subject to a maximum waiting time, the specific time for each route is published on gov.uk. The exact time taken to decide an individual case will depend on the specific circumstances of that case.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-25T16:15:25.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927727/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927727/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927727/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, for what reasons there are differences in the length of time that it takes to process indefinite leave to remain applications and applications for other forms of leave to remain.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","155908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927728","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-28","<p>The Human Fertilisation and Embryology Authority and the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency have advised that this information is not collected centrally.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-06-28T15:03:58.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927728/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927728/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927728/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","In Vitro Fertilisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many women have been administered (a) intra-lipids, (b) intravenous immunoglobulins and (c) other off-label medications from licensed IVF clinics in each year since 2014.","false","Biography information for Siobhain McDonagh","Mitcham and Morden","Siobhain McDonagh","155664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927729","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-25","<p>All United Kingdom commercial helicopter operators require an Air Operator Certificate (AOC) issued by the Civil Aviation Authority. The requirements for the granting of an AOC are set out in legislation, and are concerned with an operator’s ability to fulfil their responsibilities for safety. This approval process is not designed to take into account the environmental effect of individual flights. It would not be possible to take the views of affected residents into account because the AOC is not based on specific flying routes. Affected people with concerns over airspace or environmental effects, can inform the CAA using the <a href="http://www.caa.co.uk/default.aspx?catid=810&amp;pagetype=90" target="_blank">Airspace Use Report (FCS 1521) form</a> which can be downloaded from its website.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-06-25T11:38:59.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927729/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927729/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927729/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-20","Helicopters: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of making Civil Aviation Authority helicopter tourist flight licenses subject to appeals by residents affected by those flights.","false","Biography information for Wera Hobhouse","Bath","Wera Hobhouse","155900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927730","Home Office","false","2018-06-28","<p>As I announced on 18 June, the Government is establishing an expert panel of clinicians to advise Ministers on any applications to prescribe cannabis-based medicines. This is intended to ensure that advice to Ministers on licensing in these cases is clinically led, based firmly on medical evidence and as swift as possible. <br>The Chief Medical Officers across the UK have already been actively working together on the panel, and the expert panel will start considering applications within a week. <br>Further details, including who can apply to the panel and what information will be available to guide applicants will be confirmed in due course</p><p>The total number of staff required to process applications is yet to be confirmed.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-06-28T11:49:54.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927730/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927730/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927730/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Cannabis: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate he has made of the number of staff his Department will require to process applications for medicinal cannabis; what estimate he has made of the number of such applications that will be made; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","155767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927731","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-25","<p>The annual Association of Directors of Adult Social Services (ADASS) Budget Survey is an important resource in understanding the concerns of local authorities in relation to adult social care. The Department regularly meets with representatives from the Association and, in partnership with the Local Government Association; ADASS delivers a programme of sector led improvement in social care on behalf of the Department.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will set out further proposals for social care reform in due course, alongside the 10-year National Health Service plan. We will take into account representations such as the ADASS Budget Survey into account as we consider these.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-06-25T14:09:16.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927731/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927731/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927731/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","Social Services: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the findings of the survey conducted by the Association of Directors of Adult Social Care (ADASS) entitled ADASS Budget Survey 2018; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","155796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927732","Home Office","false","2018-06-27","<p>The United Kingdom has a statutory obligation to provide destitute asylum seekers with accommodation, transportation and cash/subsistence support whilst their application for asylum is being considered. UKVI discharges their statutory duty via a suite of COMPASS contracts with three providers; G4S, Serco and Clearsprings Ready Homes. UKVI do not accommodate service users in privately run asylum housing properties</p><p>Accommodation providers are required to provide safe, habitable, fit for purpose and correctly equipped accommodation that complies with the Decent Homes Standard in addition to standards outlined in relevant national or local housing legislation</p><p>The contract requires Providers to inspect each property every month and UKVI inspects a significant proportion of properties each year to ensure standards are being met. Where asylum accommodation is found to be falling short of the required standards UKVI has procedures in place to hold suppliers to account to quickly resolve the issue.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","155944","2018-06-27T13:17:43.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927732/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927732/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927732/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Asylum: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether his Department was aware of recent concerns raised about cockroaches, rodents and bedbugs and other substandard environmental conditions in privately-run asylum housing properties; and for what reason such properties nonetheless passed all compliance regulations and local authority property standards.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","155943"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927733","Home Office","false","2018-06-27","<p>The United Kingdom has a statutory obligation to provide destitute asylum seekers with accommodation, transportation and cash/subsistence support whilst their application for asylum is being considered. UKVI discharges their statutory duty via a suite of COMPASS contracts with three providers; G4S, Serco and Clearsprings Ready Homes. UKVI do not accommodate service users in privately run asylum housing properties</p><p>Accommodation providers are required to provide safe, habitable, fit for purpose and correctly equipped accommodation that complies with the Decent Homes Standard in addition to standards outlined in relevant national or local housing legislation</p><p>The contract requires Providers to inspect each property every month and UKVI inspects a significant proportion of properties each year to ensure standards are being met. Where asylum accommodation is found to be falling short of the required standards UKVI has procedures in place to hold suppliers to account to quickly resolve the issue.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","155943","2018-06-27T13:17:43.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927733/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927733/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927733/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Asylum: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans his Department has to review the compliance regulations and local authority property standards of privately-run asylum housing properties.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","155944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927734","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-25","<p>The Government has made no such assessment of our policies. We regret the disruption European air traffic control strikes have on passengers and recognise that their effects need to be mitigated by wherever possible. NATS, the UKs en route air navigation service provider, is working actively with other European air navigation service providers to do what it can to mitigate the effect of strikes.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-06-25T12:10:52.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927734/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927734/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927734/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-20","Air Traffic Control: France","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the findings of the recent French Parliament report by Vincent Capo-Canellas which estimates that one third of European flight delays are caused by French air traffic control.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","155800"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927735","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-25","<p>The recent delays at Felixstowe are a matter for the port to resolve. I understand that steps are being taken to rectify the problem and the situation is already improving.</p><p> </p><p>The delays do not impact on government’s market led port policy that sees a successful, competitive port sector. As such we continue to welcome the ongoing private sector investment at the Port of Felixstowe to enhance both its physical and digital infrastructure for the long term, whilst port development elsewhere means vessels were able to call at other suitable UK ports as needed.</p><p> </p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-06-25T13:15:13.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927735/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927735/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927735/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-20","Ports: Felixstowe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the delays and cancellations caused by the implementation of the new nGen terminal IT system at the port of Felixstowe.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","155801"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927736","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-29","<p>In setting the figures published in draft regulations alongside the Civil Liability Bill, the Government considered a number of factors including both the suggested guidelines for compensation set by the judiciary and the average levels of whiplash compensation paid, as well as the overall Government objectives to control costs and benefit consumers through reduced premiums. The tariff amounts have been up-rated to reflect changes in the recently published 14<sup>th</sup> Edition of Judicial College Guidelines. The final figures will be set by regulations which will be debated by Parliament through the affirmative resolution procedure, subject to the successful passage of the Bill.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-06-29T12:58:25.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927736/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927736/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927736/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-20","Personal Injury: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, by what measure the rates in the tariff of fixed compensation for soft tissue injury have been determined.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","155864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927737","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-26","<p>The number of complaints received and investigated from August 2016 to May 2018 is 7835.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2018-06-26T10:49:58.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927737/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927737/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927737/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many complaints her Department has received from people affected by legislative changes in 1995 and 2011 to the women's state pension age.","false","Biography information for Mr Stephen Hepburn","Jarrow","Mr Stephen Hepburn","155691"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927738","Home Office","false","2018-06-27","<p>The cost to process the biometric residence permit has been included as part of the overall application fee since 2008. Individuals seeking to upgrade legacy documents or replace their biometric residence permits are required to cover the cost of processing the application. There are some limited concessions for certain applicants, such as refugees.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-27T13:20:01.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927738/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927738/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927738/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, for what reason people with indefinite leave to remain do not receive (a) biometric cards and (b) no time limit status (a) automatically and (b) free of charge.","false","Biography information for Darren Jones","Bristol North West","Darren Jones","155917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927739","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-25","<p>We do not plan to collect this information.</p><p> </p><p>However, the latest Universal Credit Full Service Claimant Survey published on 8 June 2018, found that the majority of claimants found the claim process either very or fairly easy.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-06-25T15:25:17.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927739/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927739/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927739/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether her Department plans to collect information on the number of people (a) failing and (b) ceasing to claim universal credit as a result of the complexity of the process.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","155690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927740","Treasury","false","2018-06-25","<p>The government does not collect data on share schemes of EU countries, so no comparative assessment has been made. The UK has four tax advantaged employee share ownership schemes. Statistics on the use of these schemes are published here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employee-share-schemes-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employee-share-schemes-statistics</a></p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-06-25T13:36:31.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927740/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927740/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927740/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-20","Employee Ownership","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what comparative assessment he has made of the number of employee share ownership schemes in (a) the UK and (b) other EU countries.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","155700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927741","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-25","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 21 May 2018 to Question <a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2018-05-15/144155/" target="_blank">UIN 144155</a>.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-25T13:54:16.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927741/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927741/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927741/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Personal Independence Payment: Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment she has made of the effect of the three-month delay before receiving support on the financial security of young people with cancer applying for personal independence payments, and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","155667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927742","Home Office","false","2018-06-27","<p>The requested information is not published by the Home Office, and could only be compiled manually and at a disproportionate cost.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-27T13:16:31.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927742/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927742/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927742/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Migrant Workers: Deportation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many migrant workers have been deported as a result of (a) exceeding their 20-day annual limit on unpaid leave from work and (b) participating in strike action.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","155668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927743","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-25","<p>The Government has always been clear that it would prefer animals to be slaughtered close to the point of production. Our manifesto made it clear that we would take early steps to control the export of live farm animals for slaughter, once we leave the European Union (EU).</p><p> </p><p>We recently launched a call for evidence on the control of live animal exports for slaughter and on improving animal welfare during transport for all purposes including fattening after the UK leaves the EU. The call for evidence closed on 22 May 2018 and we are currently analysing the responses. The Government has also asked the Farm Animal Welfare Committee (FAWC) to look at what improvements could be made to the transport regulatory regime for all animals and for all purposes, we hope to receive the recommendations from the FAWC later in the year.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-06-25T13:44:38.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927743/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927743/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927743/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-06-20","Livestock: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans he has to ensure that the proposed ban on live animal exports will prevent live exports for the purpose of fattening.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","155669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927744","Home Office","false","2018-06-25","<p>Almost all asylum claims are processed in the community. Those who have their claim processed in detention are those who claim only after having been detained for removal, or who are detained for public protection reasons. We may also detain failed asylum seekers for removal if they refuse to leave the UK voluntarily.</p><p>In all cases, the appropriateness of detention is considered through regular reviews and whenever there is new evidence about removability or vulnerability. Detention is kept to the shortest period necessary. It may be maintained only whilst there is a realistic prospect of removal within a reasonable period of time.</p><p>There are no plans to review the Discretionary Leave policy.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-25T16:17:45.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927744/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927744/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927744/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Asylum: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will make it his policy to grant discretionary leave to remain in the UK to asylum seekers who have waited a year or longer at immigration detention centres .","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","155670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927745","Home Office","false","2018-06-27","<p>The Government values the contribution which migrants makes to the NHS</p><p>We have commissioned the independent Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) to advise on the economic and social impacts of the UK’s exit from the EU and also on how the UK’s immigration system should be aligned with a modern industrial strategy. <br>The Government will want to ensure that decisions on the long-term arrangements are based on evidence. The commission that we have asked the MAC to undertake is very much part of this. The MAC are due to publish their final report by September 2018.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-27T13:18:36.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927745/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927745/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927745/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","NHS: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Office, what plans he has to ensure that the number of medical professionals entering the UK to work in the NHS in understaffed positions including interventional radiology is maintained when the UK leave the EU.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","155671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927746","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-27","<p>Interventional radiology is a sub-specialty of clinical radiology. In the Cancer Workforce Plan for England which was published in December 2017, Health Education England (HEE) set out the case for the need to target additional training support for clinical radiology, histopathology, oncology and diagnostic and therapeutic radiography.</p><p> </p><p>As committed to in the Cancer Workforce Plan, HEE increased the number of clinical radiology training programmes by 35 in 2017, which will lead to 35 additional clinical radiology posts each year for the next five years.</p><p> </p><p>Clinical radiology has achieved a 100% fill rate over the last four years. HEE will consider whether further action is required to increase net supply beyond 2021 in the light of the longer-term workforce strategy.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","155674","2018-06-27T13:29:54.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927746/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927746/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927746/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","Radiology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if he will make it his policy to increase the number of funded training places for radiologists in order to be provide continuous interventional radiology services throughout the country.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","155672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927747","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-27","<p>The Department continues to monitor and analyse overall staffing levels across the National Health Service and adult social care, and we are working across Government to ensure there will continue to be sufficient staff to deliver the high quality services on which patients rely following the United Kingdom’s exit from the European Union.</p><p> </p><p>On 8 December the UK and EU Commission reached an agreement which delivered on the Prime Minister’s number one priority, to safeguard the rights of people who have built their lives in the UK and EU, following the UK’s exit from the EU.</p><p> </p><p>The latest nationality statistics show as at March 2018 4,558 more EU nationals excluding the UK (EU27) employed in NHS trusts and Clinical Commissioning Groups than in June 2016.</p><p> </p><p>The agreement will guarantee the rights of the 158,000 EU nationals working in our health and care system. It means that EU citizens living lawfully in the UK and UK nationals living lawfully in the EU by 29 March 2019 will be able to stay and enjoy broadly the same rights and benefits as they do now.</p><p> </p><p>In addition to this, my Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for the Home Department (Sajid Javid) recently announced that doctors and nurses have been removed from the Tier 2 visa cap, meaning the NHS will be able to recruit to understaffed medical positions.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-06-27T16:03:40.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927747/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927747/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927747/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","NHS: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans he has to ensure that the UK's withdrawal from the EU does not adversely affect the number of medical professionals entering the UK to work in the NHS in (a) interventional radiology and (b) other understaffed positions.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","155673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927748","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-27","<p>Interventional radiology is a sub-specialty of clinical radiology. In the Cancer Workforce Plan for England which was published in December 2017, Health Education England (HEE) set out the case for the need to target additional training support for clinical radiology, histopathology, oncology and diagnostic and therapeutic radiography.</p><p> </p><p>As committed to in the Cancer Workforce Plan, HEE increased the number of clinical radiology training programmes by 35 in 2017, which will lead to 35 additional clinical radiology posts each year for the next five years.</p><p> </p><p>Clinical radiology has achieved a 100% fill rate over the last four years. HEE will consider whether further action is required to increase net supply beyond 2021 in the light of the longer-term workforce strategy.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","155672","2018-06-27T13:29:54.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927748/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927748/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927748/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","Radiology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans he has to mitigate the disparity between the number of interventional radiology consultants working in the NHS and the increasing demand for interventional radiology procedures throughout England.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","155674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927749","Home Office","false","2018-06-27","<p>As is standard for government’s approach to delivery of programmes, we have in place project management tools designed to detect and mitigate risks, provide additional confidence and ensure safe delivery of the registration scheme for EU citizens after the UK leaves the EU</p><p>We will be providing further detail on the scheme in due course.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-27T13:32:40.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927749/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927749/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927749/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether his Department has carried out a risk assessment of the planned registration scheme for EU citizens after the UK leaves the EU; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","155841"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927750","Department for Education","false","2018-06-25","<p>Schools that receive two or more successive overall Requires Improvement grades, and academies judged to require special measures which are not rebrokered to a new sponsor trust, normally receive a monitoring visit from Ofsted within 30 months following publication of the last Ofsted report. Ofsted also carries out risk assessments of schools which informs the timing of any inspection. This work is resourced from Ofsted’s overall financial settlement, agreed at Spending Review, and published in Ofsted’s Annual Report and Accounts.</p><p> </p><p>The Department, through Regional School Commissioners, is responsible for oversight of academies; local authorities are responsible for oversight of maintained schools. For local authorities, the Department introduced a £50 million per year brokering and monitoring grant in November 2016, for two years. This grant has been allocated to local authorities since September 2017 to allow them to continue to monitor the performance of maintained schools, broker school improvement provision and intervene as appropriate.</p><p> </p><p>Ofsted’s board reports directly to parliament, principally through Ofsted’s published annual performance report and Education Select Committee hearings. The effectiveness of the Chair is reviewed by the Permanent Secretary of the Department for Education on behalf of the Secretary of State, taking account of a range of views. As set out in Ofsted’s Corporate Governance Framework, the Chair of the Ofsted Board is responsible for assessing the performance of individual board members.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-06-25T16:01:48.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927750/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927750/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927750/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-06-20","Schools: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent assessment he has made of the (a) adequacy of resources provided to local education authorities and Ofsted to monitor schools between Ofsted inspections and (b) the effectiveness of Ofsted boards of governors.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","155726"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927751","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-25","<p>Defra produces annual estimates of Farm Business Incomes in England with corresponding figures produced by the Welsh Government, Scottish Government and Department of Agriculture, Environment and Rural Affairs in Northern Ireland.</p><p> </p><p>Farm Business Incomes represent the financial return to all unpaid labour on their capital invested in the farm business, including land and buildings and in essence is the same as Net Profit.</p><p> </p><p>Farm Business Incomes compare the financial position and physical and economic performance of commercial farm businesses.</p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="6"><p>Average income per farm by country and farm type in 2016/2017 (a) £ per farm</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>March/February year</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>England</p></td><td><p>Wales</p></td><td><p>Scotland</p></td><td><p>Northern Ireland</p></td><td><p>United Kingdom</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>All farms (incl horticulture)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>38,000</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>24,500</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>26,500</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>22,000</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>33,000</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>by type: Cereals</p></td><td><p>43,000</p></td><td><p>..</p></td><td><p>20,500</p></td><td><p>16,500</p></td><td><p>41,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>General cropping</p></td><td><p>70,000</p></td><td><p>..</p></td><td><p>47,000</p></td><td><p>27,500</p></td><td><p>65,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dairy</p></td><td><p>50,000</p></td><td><p>31,500</p></td><td><p>34,500</p></td><td><p>23,500</p></td><td><p>40,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Grazing livestock (lowland)</p></td><td><p>16,000</p></td><td><p>22,500</p></td><td><p>18,500</p></td><td><p>16,500</p></td><td><p>17,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Grazing livestock (LFA)</p></td><td><p>27,000</p></td><td><p>23,000</p></td><td><p>23,500</p></td><td><p>21,500</p></td><td><p>24,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Specialist pigs</p></td><td><p>58,000</p></td><td><p>..</p></td><td><p>..</p></td><td><p>58,500</p></td><td><p>58,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Specialist poultry</p></td><td><p>54,000</p></td><td><p>..</p></td><td><p>..</p></td><td><p>..</p></td><td><p>54,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mixed</p></td><td><p>29,000</p></td><td><p>..</p></td><td><p>24,000</p></td><td><p>27,500</p></td><td><p>28,000</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="6"><p>. . means 'not available' or 'not applicable'.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="6"><p>(a) Figures rounded to nearest £500</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="6"><p>Source: Agriculture in the United Kingdom 2017</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-06-25T14:49:52.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927751/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927751/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927751/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-06-20","Farmers: Income","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what information his Department holds on the average income per farm in (a) Wales, (b) England, (c) Scotland, (d) Northern Ireland and (e) the UK.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","155692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927752","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-27","<p>Public Health England has provided regular updates to Ministers on the helpline and the latest number of calls to the helpline at 20 June 2018 is 53,167. Some calls have required a range of different follow-up actions including conversations with clinical specialists, details of previous screens to be checked and arrangements for a further screen to be made.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-27T13:37:56.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927752/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927752/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927752/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","Breast Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department is monitoring the (a) number, (b) nature and (c) outcomes of calls to the breast cancer screening helpline; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","155842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927753","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-27","<p>The staff who answer the initial calls to the helpline are part of a call handling service with specific training for this issue. When specialist input is required, the call-handler arranges for a follow-up call from a professionally qualified person who is usually a nurse.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-27T13:38:56.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927753/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927753/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927753/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","Breast Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what qualifications are required of the staff answering calls to the breast cancer screening helpline.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","155843"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927754","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-27","<p>Some relatives of women who have died have contacted Public Health England and they have been offered advice and support. A clinical assessment of the women who have been diagnosed with breast cancer and did not receive a final invitation for screening between 2009 and 2018 has commenced and for the women who have died, the next of kin will be contacted and offered the chance to have the outcome of the assessment explained.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-27T13:40:12.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927754/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927754/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927754/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","Breast Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assistance his Department has provided for the relatives of women who died after not being called for mammograms under the national screening programme.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","155844"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927755","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-27","<p>The women who have contacted the helpline are offered a range of information and support, including access to a conversation with a health professional that can provide further advice.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-27T13:41:20.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927755/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927755/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927755/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","Breast Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what support has been provided for women contacting the breast cancer screening helpline who should have been offered screening appointments under the national mammogram programme but were not and have since developed breast cancer.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","155845"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927756","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-27","<p>On 2 May my Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care reported to Parliament a serious failure in the national breast screening programme in England and announced an independent review to investigate and report on the circumstances of the breast screening failure, which will include establishing the timeline of relevant events from 2009 to 2018 of the Age X trial and the national programme, including their administration and governance. The review will also assess the governance, assurance and accountability processes.</p><p> </p><p>Lynda Thomas, chief executive of Macmillan Cancer Support, and Professor Martin Gore, consultant medical oncologist and professor of cancer medicine at the Royal Marsden, have been appointed as independent chairs and Peter Wyman from the Care Quality Commission has been appointed as the Vice Chair.</p><p> </p><p>The terms of reference have been published with the Written Ministerial Statement (<a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2018-06-04/HCWS731/" target="_blank">HCWCS731</a>) on 4 June 2018, and the review is due to report in November 2018.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-27T13:31:18.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927756/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927756/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927756/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","Breast Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment his Department has made of the reasons for the computer failure in the breast cancer screening programme.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","155846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927757","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-27","<p>The Defence Fire and Rescue Project will deliver improvements in the safety of firefighter personnel through greater investment in improved firefighting technology, training and equipment whilst ensuring the Ministry of Defence continues to receive the global fire and rescue capability it needs.</p><p>Bidder proposals for the project were evaluated by subject matter experts against criteria which included technical deliverability, commercial and financial aspects. The proposals have also been subject to a rigorous scrutiny, assurance and approvals process undertaken by Ministry of Defence, Cabinet Office and HM Treasury staff.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-06-27T15:08:29.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927757/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927757/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927757/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-20","Defence Fire and Rescue Service: Capita","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the award of the Defence Fire and Rescue Project contract to Capita and previous contracts with that company withdrawn or ended by the Government early, what assessment his Department has made of the ability of Capita to deliver (a) that service and (b) value for money in the delivery of that service.","false","Biography information for Gareth Snell","Stoke-on-Trent Central","Gareth Snell","155898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927758","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-27","<p>Capita's proposal has been subjected to the fullest range of testing and scrutiny across Government to ensure that the services will be delivered in a sustainable and resilient manner.</p><p>Maintaining contingency plans is Defence's routine approach when outsourcing and this includes the Defence Fire and Rescue project in the event of a change in circumstances with Capita. The contingency plans ensure that if the contract was to fail there would be minimal disruption to the delivery of appropriate fire risk management services to Defence.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-06-27T15:06:35.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927758/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927758/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927758/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-20","Defence Fire and Rescue Service: Capita","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what contingency plans his Department has in place in the event that Capita is unable to complete the Defence Fire and Rescue Project contract.","false","Biography information for Gareth Snell","Stoke-on-Trent Central","Gareth Snell","155899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927759","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-27","<p>Public Health England (PHE) has not made an assessment of the extent to which people can identify whether they have a cervix, prostate gland or ovaries.</p><p> </p><p>In July 2017, PHE published a leaflet that explains the National Health Service population screening programmes available to transgender and non-binary people in England; this can be accessed at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/nhs-population-screening-information-for-transgender-people" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/nhs-population-screening-information-for-transgender-people</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","155848 ; 155849","2018-06-27T13:42:58.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927759/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927759/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927759/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","Cervical Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to Cancer Research UK's campaign on cervical screening announced on 11 June 2018, what assessment his Department has made of the ability of people to identify whether they have a cervix.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","155847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927760","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-27","<p>Public Health England (PHE) has not made an assessment of the extent to which people can identify whether they have a cervix, prostate gland or ovaries.</p><p> </p><p>In July 2017, PHE published a leaflet that explains the National Health Service population screening programmes available to transgender and non-binary people in England; this can be accessed at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/nhs-population-screening-information-for-transgender-people" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/nhs-population-screening-information-for-transgender-people</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","155847 ; 155849","2018-06-27T13:42:58.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927760/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927760/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927760/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","Prostate Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment his Department has made of the extent to which people know whether they have a prostate gland.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","155848"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927761","Treasury","false","2018-06-28","<p>Together with the wider support the government provides, the company car tax system aims to encourage the uptake and manufacture of ultra-low emission vehicles (ULEVs) by providing an incentive for motorists to choose zero-emission and other low CO<sub>2</sub> emitting models.</p><p> </p><p>In 2017, sales of ULEVs were 1.8% of all new cars, and the UK was the second largest market for ULEVs in the EU.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-28T09:54:20.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927761/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927761/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927761/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-20","Company Cars: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the company car tax rate on consumer demand for electric vehicles.","false","Biography information for Mark Pawsey","Rugby","Mark Pawsey","155783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927762","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-27","<p>Public Health England (PHE) has not made an assessment of the extent to which people can identify whether they have a cervix, prostate gland or ovaries.</p><p> </p><p>In July 2017, PHE published a leaflet that explains the National Health Service population screening programmes available to transgender and non-binary people in England; this can be accessed at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/nhs-population-screening-information-for-transgender-people" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/nhs-population-screening-information-for-transgender-people</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","155847 ; 155848","2018-06-27T13:42:58.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927762/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927762/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927762/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","Ovarian Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment his Department has made of the extent to which people are able to identify whether they have ovaries.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","155849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927763","Treasury","false","2018-06-28","<p>As confirmed in the Government response to the joint report of the Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, Environmental Audit, Health and Social Care, and Transport Committees, the Government is committed to tackling climate change and air pollution. HMT sees tax and spending policy as playing an important role in achieving this, alongside other approaches such as regulation. The full government response to this report has been published here: <a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/committees/committees-a-z/commons-select/environment-food-and-rural-affairs-committee/news-parliament-2017/joint-air-quality-response-publication-17-19/" target="_blank">https://www.parliament.uk/business/committees/committees-a-z/commons-select/environment-food-and-rural-affairs-committee/news-parliament-2017/joint-air-quality-response-publication-17-19/</a></p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-28T09:58:24.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927763/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927763/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927763/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-20","Air Pollution","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the joint report of the Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, Environmental Audit, Health and Social Care, and Transport Committees entitled Improving Air Quality, published on 15 March 2018, HC 433, what steps the Government has taken in response to the recommendation in that report to more closely align fiscal incentives with policy objectives on air quality.","false","Biography information for Mark Pawsey","Rugby","Mark Pawsey","155784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927764","Treasury","false","2018-06-28","<p>At Autumn Budget 2017, the government announced that it would legislate, in a future Finance Bill, for the Worldwide Harmonised Light Vehicle Test Procedure (WLTP) to be introduced from April 2020.</p><p> </p><p>Officials are working with industry to determine the effect of the move to WLTP and the equivalent New European Driving Cycle values.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-28T09:56:18.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927764/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927764/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927764/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-20","Company Cars: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment HM Treasury has made of the effect of the new Worldwide Harmonised Light Vehicle Test Procedure emissions standard and the use of correlated New European Drive Cycle values on Company Car Tax bands.","false","Biography information for Mark Pawsey","Rugby","Mark Pawsey","155785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927765","Department for International Trade","false","2018-07-04","<p>The whole of the Department for International Trade (DIT) supports trade and export promotion. As at 31 May 2018, the total workforce currently engaged in delivering DIT objectives in DIT is 3,781. This is the highest it has been since the department was created. This number includes staff working overseas and includes staff working in UK Export Finance.</p><p> </p><p>DIT has recently updated its methodology for reporting on its workforce to be consistent with standard approaches across government.</p>","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery",,"2018-07-04T16:53:40.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927765/answer","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927765/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927765/answer","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927765/answer/previousversion/65587","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-06-20","Department for International Trade: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what the maximum number of full-time equivalent staff employed in trade and export promotion in his Department has been; and what the current complement of such staff is.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","155647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927766","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-28","<p>I welcome Crisis's report and Government shares the broad ambition it sets out. That is why we have committed to halving rough sleeping by 2022 and ending it by 2027. As part of this we have established the Rough Sleeping Advisory Panel and a cross-Government Ministerial Taskforce to support the development and implementation of the Rough Sleeping Strategy. Crisis sit on the Advisory Panel and supported the work to put forward a number of recommendations for the Rough Sleeping Strategy.</p><p>I will continue to consider the findings outlined within the report ahead of the publication of the Rough Sleeping Strategy. My Department will also continue to work with Crisis once the strategy has been published and remain committed to tackling both rough sleeping and broader issues of homelessness as highlighted in the report.</p>","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams",,"2018-06-28T10:34:29.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927766/answer","Biography information for Nigel Adams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927766/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927766/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-06-20","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the validity of the findings in the Crisis report, Everybody In: How to end homelessness in Great Britain.","false","Biography information for Faisal Rashid","Warrington South","Faisal Rashid","155939"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927767","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-07-03","<p>Universal Credit delivers value for money. As the business case makes clear, Universal Credit will create net economic benefits of £34 billion over the ten years to 2026-27, for example by helping 200,000 more people into work. 83% of Universal Credit claimants are satisfied with the service that they receive.</p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-07-03T16:40:17.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927767/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927767/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927767/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment she has made of the validity of the assessment by the National Audit Office of the value for money of universal credit.","false","Biography information for Faisal Rashid","Warrington South","Faisal Rashid","155940"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927768","Treasury","false","2018-06-28","<p>From 2020/21, the government will be introducing eleven new company car tax bands for ultra-low emission vehicles (ULEVs). These changes were announced at Autumn Statement 2016 to provide certainty of the future tax liability for company car employers and employees.</p><p> </p><p>The government aims to announce the company car tax rates three years in advance of implementation.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","155787","2018-06-28T09:52:23.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927768/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927768/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927768/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-20","Company Cars: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he plans to announce the rates of company car tax which will apply from April 2021.","false","Biography information for Mark Pawsey","Rugby","Mark Pawsey","155786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927769","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-25","<p>No specific assessment has been made of Bristol Channel shipping routes. In the first instance shipping services are undertaken on a private sector basis. The choice of routes operated will therefore be dependent on potential market volumes, competition and the commercial viability of these.</p><p> </p><p>Some, very limited funding support via Waterborne Freight Grant is available for coastal shipping, in recognition of its wider benefits over road transport. Recent research is planned to be published about potential changes to this support regime.</p><p> </p><p>The recent Department for Transport report <em>“Transport Infrastructure for our global future: a study of England’s port connectivity”</em>, has committed to work with the maritime industry to better understand the barriers, challenges and market opportunities for coastal shipping.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-06-25T13:35:24.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927769/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927769/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927769/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-20","Shipping: Bristol Channel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment he has made of the potential for a modal shift from road to sea through the revival of shipping routes in the Bristol Channel between ports in Wales and England.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","155833"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927770","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-25","<p>The Government has no current plans to lower the drink drive limit and considers rigorous enforcement and serious penalties for drink drivers to be effective deterrents.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-06-25T16:10:59.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927770/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927770/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927770/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-20","Driving under Influence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of bringing drink-driving limits in England and Wales in line with those in Northern Ireland and Scotland.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","155932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927771","Home Office","false","2018-06-27","<p><br>NHS workforce statistics are the responsibility of NHS Digital and are published at <a href="https://digital.nhs.uk/data-and-information/publications/statistical/nhs-workforce-statistics/nhs-workforce-statistics-june-2017-provisional-statistics" target="_blank">https://digital.nhs.uk/data-and-information/publications/statistical/nhs-workforce-statistics/nhs-workforce-statistics-june-2017-provisional-statistics</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","155934","2018-06-27T13:34:15.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927771/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927771/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927771/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Doctors: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many doctors working in the UK on a Tier 2 visa work in the NHS.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","155933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927772","Home Office","false","2018-06-27","<p><br>NHS workforce statistics are the responsibility of NHS Digital and are published at <a href="https://digital.nhs.uk/data-and-information/publications/statistical/nhs-workforce-statistics/nhs-workforce-statistics-june-2017-provisional-statistics" target="_blank">https://digital.nhs.uk/data-and-information/publications/statistical/nhs-workforce-statistics/nhs-workforce-statistics-june-2017-provisional-statistics</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","155933","2018-06-27T13:34:15.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927772/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927772/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927772/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Nurses: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many nurses working in the UK on a Tier 2 visa work in the NHS.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","155934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927773","Home Office","false","2018-06-26","<p>On Friday 15 June, the Government announced changes to the allocation of places within the Tier 2 (General) cap of 20,700. The change – which will be implemented through amended Immigration Rules coming into effect on 6 July – will ensure that all doctors and all nurses needed in the UK will be able to be recruited to work here without being counted against the cap. This is intended to be a temporary change which recognises the importance of alleviating pressure on the NHS and which creates extra space within the cap for other sectors of the economy, including highly skilled veterinarians. <br> <br>In parallel, we have asked the independent Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) to review the full composition of the Shortage Occupation List.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-26T11:36:32.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927773/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927773/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927773/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Migrant Workers: Veterinary Medicine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether the lifting of restrictions on the allocation of Tier 2 visas will apply to highly skilled veterinarians.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","155851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927774","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-25","<p>Information on informal observations and their use in reaching a decision is not collected centrally. To establish an estimate would require a manual examination of each individual assessment report form and decision.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","155825","2018-06-25T14:30:34.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927774/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927774/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927774/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the answer of 6 June 2018 to Question 150695 on Personal Independence Payment, where that information is collated.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","155824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927775","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-29","<p>In November 2017, Network Rail announced the sale of its commercial estate business in England and Wales. It is a non-core property asset, which produces commercial income for Network Rail and is not essential for running the railway.</p><p>Network Rail manages its commercial estate as a commercial business. Its rents are set with reference to local property market conditions. Rent reviews happen on a periodic basis as outlined in tenants’ leases and in accordance with normal commercial property market practice.</p><p>Once the business is sold, all current leases will transfer to the new buyer and all lease arrangements will be unchanged. The tenants’ notice period will also continue as per their original lease agreement. Tenants will continue to be subject to rent reviews as they are currently and as outlined above.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-29T09:17:35.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927775/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927775/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927775/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-20","Network Rail: Property","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 19 June 2018 to Question 152257 on Network Rail: Property, what protections will be afforded to Network Rail tenants in relation to future rent increases after the sale of Network Rail’s arches estate.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","155878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927776","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-25","<p>Information on informal observations and their use in reaching a decision is not collected centrally. To establish an estimate would require a manual examination of each individual assessment report form and decision.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","155824","2018-06-25T14:30:34.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927776/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927776/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927776/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the answer of 6 June 2018 to Question 150695 on Personal Independence Payment, what information her Department holds on the number of personal independence payment assessment reports that (a) have included consideration of informal observations and (b) used informal observations to come to a decision in each year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","155825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927777","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-25","<p>As outlined in the Written Statements of 19<sup>th</sup> January 2018 (<a href="https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2018-01-19/debates/18011939000006/Welfare" target="_blank">HCWS414</a>) and 15<sup>th</sup> June 2018 (<a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2018-06-15/HCWS767/" target="_blank">HCWS767</a>), my Department will be carrying out administrative exercises to identify anyone who may be entitled to more as a result of the judgments.</p><p> </p><p>The administrative cost will depend on a number of factors, including the number of cases identified.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-25T14:44:33.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927777/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927777/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927777/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what additional (a) resources and (b) funding her Department has been allocated to process back-dated claims for personal independence payments.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","155826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927778","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-28","<p>The report published by the National Audit Office, published March 2018, clearly sets out what resources and funding we have allocated to this process. The relevant information can be found at paragraphs 2.17 and 2.19:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.nao.org.uk/report/investigation-into-errors-in-employment-and-support-allowance/" target="_blank">https://www.nao.org.uk/report/investigation-into-errors-in-employment-and-support-allowance/</a></p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-28T16:44:46.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927778/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927778/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927778/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what additional (a) resources and (b) funding her Department has been allocated to process back-dated claims for employment support allowance.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","155827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927779","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-25","<p>As outlined in the Written Statement of 15<sup>th</sup> June 2018 (<a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2018-06-15/HCWS767/" target="_blank">HCWS767</a>), the department will be conducting an administrative exercise to identify claimants who may be affected by the Upper Tribunal judgment in LB.</p><p> </p><p>My Department are now working at pace and taking all steps necessary for this administrative exercise to take place later in the year.</p><p> </p><p>This administrative exercise to identify claimants who may be affected by the judgment will include all those who were in receipt of PIP or received a PIP decision during the period between the date of the LB judgment (28 November 2016) and the date of the March 2017 amendments (16 March 2017). It will include claimants currently assessed as needing support to manage medication or monitor a health condition.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-25T15:25:20.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927779/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927779/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927779/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Written Ministerial Statement of 15 June 2018 on Personal Independence Payments HCWS767, if she will publish the terms of reference for the review.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","155828"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927780","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-25","<p>The estimated number of claimants affected by the Personal Independence Payment Upper Tribunal judgments LB and RJ can be found in the following Written Statements, published on 15<sup>th</sup> June 2018 (<a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2018-06-15/HCWS767/" target="_blank">HCWS767</a>) and 2<sup>nd</sup> November 2017 (<a href="https://hansard.parliament.uk/commons/2017-11-02/debates/17110233000008/SocialSecurity" target="_blank">HCWS218</a>). For the Upper Tribunal judgment in MH, the estimated number of affected claimants can be found in the Economic and Fiscal Outlook, published by the Office for Budget Responsibility (OBR) in March 2018, p.136 <a href="http://cdn.obr.uk/EFO-MaRch_2018.pdf" target="_blank">http://cdn.obr.uk/EFO-MaRch_2018.pdf</a>.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-25T14:12:16.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927780/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927780/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927780/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate she has made of the number of people who will receive a back-payment for personal independence payment.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","155829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927781","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-28","<p>There are no current plans to review the Personal Independence Payment assessment criteria.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-28T16:44:45.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927781/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927781/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927781/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if she will undertake a review of the assessment criteria for personal independence payments.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","155830"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927782","Home Office","false","2018-06-26","<p>Employers who are unable to find suitable resident workers to fill vacancies in the UK for highly skilled social care workers can be recruited under Tier 2, our main immigration work route. <br>Social care workers working in children’s and family services are recognised as being in national shortage and continue to receive first priority within the monthly Tier 2 allocation process</p><p>On Friday 15 June, the Government announced changes to the allocation of places within the Tier 2 (General) cap of 20,700. The change, which will ensure that all doctors and all nurses needed in the UK will be able to be recruited to work here without being counted against the cap, will create extra space within the cap for other sectors of the economy, including social care workers who meet the minimum skills equirement. <br>We have asked the independent Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) to review the full composition of the Shortage Occupation List and continue to keep all immigration routes under review.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-26T11:38:49.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927782/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927782/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927782/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Migrant Workers: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will review the visa system for social care workers.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","155816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927783","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-28","<p>As a result of increased Government support, Blackburn and Darwen received an additional £7.3 million for adult social care in 2017/18.</p><p> </p><p>In total Blackburn and Darwen have access to up to £28.8 million additional funding between 2017/18 and 2019/20.</p><p> </p><p>Blackburn and Darwen’s adult social care budget for 2017/18 was £46.55 million. This is a 16.6% increase compared to the previous year.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has given councils in England access to up to £9.4 billion more dedicated funding for social care over three years.</p><p> </p><p>The action we have taken means that overall, councils are able to increase spending on adult social care in real terms for each of the three years from 2017/18.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will take decisions on funding for social care beyond 2019/20 as part of the forthcoming spending review.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-06-28T11:11:26.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927783/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927783/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927783/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","Social Services: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if he will allocate additional funding to meet the demand for social care in (a) Blackburn and (b) England ahead of the upcoming green paper on social care.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","155817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927784","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-29","<p>I am withholding details of the number of missions and hours flown by the RAF's E-3D Sentry fleet on specific taskings as disclosure would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","155702 ; 155703 ; 155707","2018-06-29T13:55:44.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927784/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927784/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927784/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-20","Middle East: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many missions Sentry aircraft were involved in in (a) Iraq and (b) Syria between September 2014 and June 2018.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","155701"
