"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927864","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-28","<p>Supporting victims of crime is a priority for the Government and we have made a commitment to publish a Victims Strategy this Summer.</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar",,"2018-06-28T13:48:01.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927864/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927864/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927864/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-20","Crime: Victims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when the consultation on victims of crime announced on 16 January 2017 will commence.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","155882"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927865","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-29","<p>Supporting victims of crime is a priority for the Government and we have made a commitment to publish a Victims Strategy this Summer. We are looking at legislative and non-legislative options to give effect to the Strategy. My predecessor met regularly with the Victims’ Commissioner and victims organisations, as well as directly with victims of crime. I will continue this engagement and I look forward to hearing from victims and those who support them.</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-06-29T12:59:51.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927865/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927865/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927865/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-20","Crime: Victims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what meetings his Department has held with victims organisations on law for victims of crime in the last twelve months.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","155883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927866","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-28","<p>The Code of Practice for Victims of Crime (Victims' Code) is issued by the Secretary of State for Justice under section 32 of the Domestic Violence, Crime and Victims Act 2004. As such, the Code exists independently of EU laws and therefore leaving the EU will not affect its operability.</p><p> </p><p>Supporting victims of crime is a priority for the Government and we have made a commitment to publish a Victims Strategy this Summer. The strategy will consider how compliance with the entitlements in the Victims’ Code might be improved and better monitored, and how those responsible for delivery of entitlements might be better held to account.</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar",,"2018-06-28T13:48:34.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927866/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927866/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927866/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-20","Crime: Victims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment he has made of the effect of leaving the EU on the (a) adherence to and (b) content of the Victims Code.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","155884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927867","Home Office","false","2018-06-28","<p>We received over 3,200 responses to the consultation. The responses are currently being analysed and we intend to publish a Government response as well as a draft Bill later this session.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-06-28T14:25:35.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927867/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927867/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927867/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the consultation on transforming the response to domestic abuse, which closed on 31 May 2018, what the timetable is for the strategy for transforming the response to domestic abuse to be published.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","155885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927868","Home Office","false","2018-06-28","<p>In March 2014 the Government rolled out the Domestic Violence Disclosure Scheme (DVDS) and Domestic Violence Protection Orders across England and Wales. <br>The DVDS enables the police to disclose to the public information about previous violent offending by a new or existing partner where this may help protect them from further violent offending. The latest figures show 3,410 disclosures have been made under DVDS. <br>Our recent domestic abuse consultation sought views on what more can be done to provide support to victims and tackle repeat perpetrators. The responses are currently being analysed and we intend to publish a Government response as well as a draft Bill later this session.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-06-28T14:29:04.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927868/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927868/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927868/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Domestic Abuse: Reoffenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what (a) protection and (b) advice is given to victims of domestic abuse in cases where the perpetrator is a repeat offender.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","155886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927869","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-28","<p>It is not possible to identify this information from centrally held Ministry of Justice data. Details such as where offences took place or the number of people involved cannot be obtained without incurring disproportionate costs as individual court records would need to be manually searched.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-06-28T13:00:28.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927869/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927869/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927869/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-20","Domestic Abuse: Convictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people were convicted in each of the last 3 years of an offence against the person relating to separate incidents in a domestic setting involving (a) two people, (b) three people and (c) four people or more.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","155887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927870","Department for International Trade","false","2018-06-29","<p>The Government does not publish data detailing the value of defence exports by individual country.</p><p>However, the estimated total of UK defence exports (based on orders/contracts signed) to Africa as a whole in each of the last three years is shown in the table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total £Mil</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>10.94</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>16.86</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>41.01</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The data is taken from the Department for International Trade’s Defence and Security Organisation (DIT DSO) official statistics which are released annually on the Gov.UK website here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics?departments%5B%5D=department-for-international-trade-defence-and-security-organisation" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics?departments%5B%5D=department-for-international-trade-defence-and-security-organisation</a>.</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart",,"2018-06-29T12:43:41.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927870/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927870/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927870/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-06-20","Arms Trade: Sub-Saharan Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what the value of British defence exports to sub Saharan Africa was in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","155909"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927871","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-25","<p>Ministers are assured on the work of NHS England and Public Health England in delivering effective screening programmes through quarterly accountability meetings, chaired by senior officials. Separate meetings review and assure progress in delivery of Public Health England’s remit letter and business plan, and of the NHS Public Health Functions Agreement with NHS England.</p><p> </p><p>Ministers are informed of the details of the statistical report on the Breast Screening Programme, England, every year, which NHS Digital publishes. Prior to January 2018 the last report was published in February 2017 for 2015/16, which is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://digital.nhs.uk/data-and-information/publications/statistical/breast-screening-programme/breast-screening-programme-england-2015-16" target="_blank">https://digital.nhs.uk/data-and-information/publications/statistical/breast-screening-programme/breast-screening-programme-england-2015-16</a></p><p> </p><p>The subsequent report for 2016/17 was published in January 2018 and is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://digital.nhs.uk/data-and-information/publications/statistical/breast-screening-programme/breast-screening-programme-england---2016-17" target="_blank">https://digital.nhs.uk/data-and-information/publications/statistical/breast-screening-programme/breast-screening-programme-england---2016-17</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-25T14:17:38.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927871/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927871/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927871/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-20","Breast Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 5 June 2018 to Question 147340, when the last occasion was before January 2018 when assurance was given to Ministers on the work undertaken by NHS England and Public Health England in delivering effective screening programmes; and what information was given to Minsters on the effectiveness of the breast screening programme.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","155683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927872","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-25","<p>Primary legislation sets out that a claimant cannot be entitled to Personal Independence Payment (PIP) for any period prior to the date of claim and payment can only commence once the three month qualifying period has been satisfied, other than for claimants who are terminally ill. Claims to PIP can be taken during the three month qualifying period meaning that some or all of the three month period may have been met prior to a claim being made.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-25T13:54:47.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927872/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927872/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927872/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Personal Independence Payment: Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if her Department will look into the feasibility of backdating personal independence payments for young cancer patients following the three-month qualifying period.","true","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","155797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927873","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-25","<p>Other than for those who are terminally ill, Disability Living Allowance (DLA) is assessed on the basis of the needs arising from a long-term health condition or disability rather than a diagnosis. The three month qualifying period is one of the tests that determines whether an individual meets that definition. Claims to PIP can be taken during the three month qualifying period meaning that some or all of the three month period may have been met prior to a claim being made</p><p> </p><p>DLA claimants who are terminally ill do not have to satisfy the three month qualifying period, have their claim fast tracked and are eligible for the higher rate care component from the date of claim.</p><p> </p><p>Financial and practical support may be available during the qualifying period, for example through the Healthcare Travel Costs Scheme or support provided by a Local Authority.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-25T15:40:20.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927873/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927873/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927873/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Disability Living Allowance: Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if she will make an assessment of the effect the three-month qualifying period for disability living allowance on families of children with cancer.","true","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","155798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927874","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-28","<p>​The UK has licensed the export of a wide range of military items to Saudi Arabia and the United Arab Emirates. These include combat aircraft and components as well as precision guided munitions that have been used by Saudi Arabia in Yemen. We do not have specific information on whether equipment licensed by the UK has been used in operations in Hodeidah. We will not licence the export of items where we assess that there is a clear risk that they might be used in the commission of a serious violation of international humanitarian law or international human rights law.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-28T16:27:14.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927874/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927874/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927874/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-20","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the Government has made an assessment of whether UK-licensed military goods were used in the Saudi-led operation in Hodeidah port; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","155910"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927875","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-29","<p>The UK has licensed the export of a variety of military equipment to Saudi Arabia. We do not have a full picture of which specific items have been used in Yemen, but some combat aircraft have been used there. Details of export licences issued to Saudi Arabia are available in the official statistics published by the Department for International Trade on <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/strategic-export-controls-licensing-data" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/collections/strategic-export-controls-licensing-data</a>.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-29T12:50:09.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927875/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927875/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927875/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-20","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Foreign and Commonwealth Office, what British-supplied military equipment has been used by the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia in Yemen since 1 January 2017.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","155911"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927876","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-25","<p>The maximum day rate relates to Senior Civil Servant (SCS) roles.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-06-25T16:21:07.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927876/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927876/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927876/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-20","Ministry of Justice: Capita","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 2 May 2018 to Question 137623 on Ministry of Justice: agency workers, for what category of work the maximum rate of £221.06 was paid to Capita.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","155870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927877","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-25","<p>We can confirm that between the periods of 2016-2018 the MoJ hasn’t paid any interim/contractor the maximum daily rate from the contracted rate card. The Maximum daily rate relates to the role of Senior Civil Servant 3.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-06-25T16:20:51.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927877/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927877/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927877/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-20","Ministry of Justice: Capita","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 2 May 2018 to Question 137623 on Ministry of Justice: agency workers, how many hours of work was paid at the maximum rate of £221.06 per hour.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","155871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927878","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-25","<p>The amount paid to Capita under agency contracts in financial years 2016/17 and 2017/18 is £102,317,539.00 as set out in the department’s annual accounts.</p><p>Staff used under this contract provide specialist skills or support for short term projects for roles where it would not be cost-effective to employ staff on a permanent basis. We are working towards reducing this spend but will continue to use such contracts to improve the delivery of our services and policy and where doing so works out better for the taxpayer.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-06-25T16:20:18.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927878/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927878/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927878/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-20","Ministry of Justice: Capita","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much was paid to Capita under agency contracts by his Department in the last two financial years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","155872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927879","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-25","<p>The financial allocation for each financial year is subject to change throughout the year, and the final expenditure in 2018/19 will be published in the 2018 Annual Report, which is expected to be published by July 2019. This is not disaggregated by Gaza and the West Bank. The UK supports stability and vulnerable Palestinian refugees through our financial assistance to the Palestinian Authority and UNRWA respectively. We are closely monitoring the situation in Gaza and the UK is supporting water and sanitation needs through £1.9 million support to UNICEF and £1.5 million to ICRC helping support patients in 11 hospitals in Gaza.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-25T12:38:53.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927879/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927879/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927879/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-06-20","Palestinians: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much financial assistance her Department has allocated to (a) Gaza and the (b) Palestinian territories in 2018.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","155818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927880","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-25","<p>Since 1 July 2017, 48 complaints concerning Universal Credit have been received from people in Blackburn.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Notes:</strong></p><p> </p><p>This data is from DWP internal management information which does not form part of the official statistics outputs that are released by the Department in accordance with the UK Statistics Authority’s Code of Practice. It relates to Tier 1 and Tier 2 complaints for both live and full service Universal Credit claims.</p><p> </p><p>Universal Credit Full Service rolled out in Blackburn on 14 February 2018.</p><p> </p><p>Blackburn Jobcentre currently has 2,808 Universal Credit Full Service claimants.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-06-25T15:40:18.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927880/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927880/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927880/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Universal Credit: Blackburn","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many complaints her Department has received in relation to universal credit from people in Blackburn.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","155819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927881","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-25","<p>The DWP complaints system does not collect information at this level of detail.</p><p> </p><p>The only way to obtain specific complaints information about Personal Independence Payment (PIP) process from people in Blackburn, would be to investigate each PIP complaint on a case by case basis. This could only be retrieved at disproportionate cost to the Department.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-25T13:55:23.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927881/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927881/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927881/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Personal Independence Payment: Blackburn","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many complaints her Department has received on the personal independence process from people in Blackburn.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","155820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927882","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-28","<p>We are confident that our robust process for assessing export licence applications manages the risk that UK-supplied equipment might be used in a way that is inconsistent with the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria. That process includes a rigorous assessment of the risks of diversion. In addition, we judge that it would not be practical or effective to carry out verification visits to end users in country. We keep extant licences under review and will revoke a licence if we judge that the export of the items covered by the licence would no longer be consistent with the Consolidated Criteria. We do not generally collect information on whether items granted an export licence are exported, or how they are then used.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-28T15:06:07.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927882/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927882/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927882/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-20","Occupied Territories","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant the Answer of 29 March 2018 to Question 133735 on Occupied Territories, for what reason the data is not being collected.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","155912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927883","Home Office","false","2018-07-02","<p>Information about individuals who have been denied access to benefits or services is not held by the Home Office.</p><p>We set up a task force in April to help people from the Windrush generation to evidence their status and access the services they are entitled to.</p><p>The Home Office has sent out communications urging other government departments and public authorities to exercise particular care when responding to applications for benefits and services from the Windrush generation. The Home Office will be notifying NHS Trusts in situations where individuals are issued with documentation by the Taskforce . This is so that the NHS trust can consider if a charge for NHS treatment was applied incorrectly and requires cancellation.</p><p>The Home Office has introduced additional safeguards to ensure those from the Windrush generation are not adversely affected by measures designed to protect benefits and services. I have chaired a cross-Whitehall meeting with relevant departments, including the Department of Health, to ensure we are all taking the relevant steps to protect the Windrush generation.</p><p>The Government is clear that where the Windrush generation have suffered loss, they will be compensated. The first stage was the launch of a Call for Evidence, that closed on 8 June. The Government will publish a further public consultation on the design and shape of the scheme, as soon as the time has been taken to analyse the responses to the Call for Evidence and use the information gathered to inform design and implementation considerations.</p><p>In the meantime, we will continue to work with and support affected individuals through the operation of the Windrush Taskforce.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-07-02T16:38:22.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927883/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927883/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927883/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-20","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate he has made of the number of Windrush generation people that were denied (a) benefits and (b) healthcare as a result of their immigration status being questioned.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","155821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927884","Scotland Office","false","2018-06-25","<p>I refer the hon Member to the answer I gave on 10 May 2018 (UIN 141353).</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-06-25T16:33:36.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927884/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927884/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927884/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-06-20","Scots Gaelic Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what steps his Department is taking to enable Gaelic speakers to complete official Government documents in their native language.","false","Biography information for Carol Monaghan","Glasgow North West","Carol Monaghan","155850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927885","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-28","<p>​As the Prime Minister said on 20 June, the reports and pictures we have seen in the past couple of days are deeply disturbing and wrong. We do not apply similar measures here and will never do so. Later on 20 June, President Trump signed an Executive Order aimed at ending the separation policy.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-06-28T14:17:29.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927885/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927885/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927885/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-20","USA: Undocumented Migrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the representatives of the US administration on that country's zero tolerance policy on illegal immigration.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","155921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927886","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-29","<p>Network Rail agreed to suspend all tree felling for the duration of the current nesting season, except where it is safety critical, on 11<sup>th</sup> May 2018. This followed my announcement on 10<sup>th</sup> May, that I would commission an independent review into Network Rail’s approach to vegetation management in England and Wales.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-29T10:22:58.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927886/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927886/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927886/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-20","Network Rail: Tree Felling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, on what date his policy to stop tree felling on Network Rail land came into force.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","155922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927887","Treasury","false","2018-06-28","<p>From 2020/21, the government will be introducing eleven new company car tax bands for ultra-low emission vehicles (ULEVs). These changes were announced at Autumn Statement 2016 to provide certainty of the future tax liability for company car employers and employees.</p><p> </p><p>The government aims to announce the company car tax rates three years in advance of implementation.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","155786","2018-06-28T09:52:23.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927887/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927887/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927887/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-20","Company Cars: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will bring forward the introduction of lower company car tax thresholds for ultra low emission vehicles.","false","Biography information for Mark Pawsey","Rugby","Mark Pawsey","155787"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927888","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-28","<p>​The UK is not involved in the Turkish-led operation in Afrin and we cannot provide comprehensive information about it. We understand that a number of different Syrian armed groups were involved in the operation with Turkish support including air support and artillery strikes.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-06-28T14:20:01.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927888/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927888/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927888/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-20","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment the Government has made of (a) which Islamist groups were involved in Turkey’s intervention in Afrin and (b) the level of collaboration between those groups and the Turkish armed forces.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","155913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927889","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-28","<p>We have been closely following Turkey's Operation Tigris Shield, announced in March in order to combat PKK fighters in the Turkey-Iraq border regions. The PKK remains a significant threat to Turkey and is an internationally proscribed terrorist organisation.</p><p>UK arms exports are subject to export controls. We have no specific information concerning whether UK-licensed items are in use in Turkish military operations in northern Iraq, but all decisions in respect of the original licences have been taken based on the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria and according to the latest information available. We keep our approach to all countries under continual review.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-06-28T14:24:31.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927889/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927889/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927889/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-20","Iraq: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment the Government has made of (a) Turkey’s military role in northern Iraq; and whether Turkish armed forces have used British military equipment in northern Iraq in 2018.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","155914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927890","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-26","<p>Ordnance Survey has been commissioned to monitor the progress of sites sold through both the 2011-15 and 2015-20 Public Land for Housing Programmes and is gathering information on the planned number of affordable homes, which will be made available in due course. Decisions on affordable housing provision are taken at a local level according to local need.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-06-26T10:24:13.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927890/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927890/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927890/answer","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927890/answer/previousversion/65505","Biography information for Dominic Raab","7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-06-20","Social Rented Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what proportion of the homes developed on surplus public land which has been sold off as part of the Public Land for Housing Programme is social housing.","false","Biography information for Matt Western","Warwick and Leamington","Matt Western","155916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927891","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-29","<p>Network Rail published its own position statement on the 11<sup>th</sup> May 2018, outlining the conditions where tree felling may continue, in accordance with Network Rail’s statutory responsibility to ensure the safe operation of the railways. This guidance states that all tree felling activity in England and Wales must cease, except where the work is safety critical.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-29T10:25:55.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927891/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927891/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927891/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-20","Network Rail: Tree Felling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, under what conditions trees on Network Rail land can still be felled.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","155923"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927892","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-25","<p>I refer the honourable member to the answer given to PQ152822 on Wednesday 20 June 2018.</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar",,"2018-06-25T14:27:51.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927892/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927892/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927892/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-20","Criminal Injuries Compensation: Offenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people have been refused compensation by the Criminal Injuries Compensation Authority for having an unspent (a) custodial sentence of a year or more, (b) custodial sentence of less than a year and (b) non-custodial sentence as punishment for the unspent conviction in 2018.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","155873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927893","Cabinet Office","false","2018-06-25","<p>The Government will publish external versions of cross-government strategies, as they are updated, where this is compatible with UK national security.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2018-06-25T14:47:01.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927893/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927893/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927893/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-06-20","National Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to recommendation two of the Capability Review of the Cross Government Funds, published on 28 March 2018, when he plans to publish the country level strategies of the National Security Strategy.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","155915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927894","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-25","<p>Since the suspension came into force on the 11<sup>th</sup> May, Network Rail has removed trees in accordance with its updated published position statement on vegetation management. This states that only safety critical tree felling can be performed on Network Rail land during the current nesting season.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-25T16:01:52.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927894/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927894/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927894/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-20","Network Rail: Tree Felling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether any tree-felling has taken place on Network Rail land since the implementation of the ban on tree felling.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","155924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927895","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-25","<p>​The British Government has taken note of the concerns across Kashmir raised in the UN High Commissioner for Human Rights' report and his recommendations for both the Governments of India and Pakistan to consider. We encourage all states to cooperate with the Office of the High Commissioner for Human Rights and ensure that their domestic laws are in line with international human rights standards.</p><p>The FCO is concerned by any allegation of human rights abuse, which much must be investigated thoroughly, promptly and transparently. The UK's longstanding position is that it is for India and Pakistan to find a lasting political resolution to the situation in Kashmir, taking account of the wishes of the Kashmiri people. It is not for the UK to prescribe a solution or act as a mediator.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-06-25T14:38:17.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927895/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927895/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927895/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-20","Kashmir: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the report entitled Report on the Situation of Human Rights in Kashmir: Developments in the Indian State of Jammu and Kashmir from June 2016 to April 2018, and General Human Rights Concerns in Azad Jammu and Kashmir and Gilgit-Baltistan, published by the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights on 14 June 2018, what steps his Department is taking to ensure the recommendations of that report is given serious consideration by the Governments of India and Pakistan.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","155831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927896","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-25","<p>Prison Governors are given responsibility for workforce planning within their establishments and for determining the number of staff at each grade.</p><p> </p><p>Individual prison budgets are agreed and allocated at the beginning of each financial year and include funding for all prison staff, including the recruitment of prison officers. The costs of recruitment of any additional officers are met from within the overall prison budgets.</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-06-25T16:57:41.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927896/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927896/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927896/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-20","Prison Officers: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 15 June 2018 to Question 150720 on Prison Officers, what additional funding has been made available to prison governors to recruit prison officers in addition to those 3,111 prison officers.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","155874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927897","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-25","<p>Special measures means HM Prisons and Probation Service has determined a prison needs additional, specialist support to improve its performance. Any additional funding provided is drawn from a range of business as usual budgets. It is not possible to identify, from those budgets, a single figure showing how much has been used to help provide support to prisons in special measures.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","155876","2018-06-25T16:25:16.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927897/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927897/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927897/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-20","Prisons: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 13 June 2018 to Question 150725 on Prisons: Standards, how much additional money has been allocated to each of the prisons in special measures in each of the last four financial years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","155875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927898","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-25","<p>Special measures means HM Prisons and Probation Service has determined a prison needs additional, specialist support to improve its performance. Any additional funding provided is drawn from a range of business as usual budgets. It is not possible to identify, from those budgets, a single figure showing how much has been used to help provide support to prisons in special measures.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","155875","2018-06-25T16:25:16.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927898/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927898/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927898/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-20","Prisons: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, Pursuant to the Answer of 13 June 2018 to Question 150725 on Prisons: Standards, how much additional money has been allocated to the prisons in special measures in each of the last four financial years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","155876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927899","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-25","<p>The UK Government has committed to protect the amount we allocate to farm support, in cash terms, until the end of this Parliament. We have also committed to introduce a new environmental land management scheme thereafter and, in England, we have already started detailed work on the design of that future scheme.</p><p> </p><p>Outside of the Common Agricultural Policy we can have an agriculture and land management policy that works for the whole of the United Kingdom and we intend to give as much flexibility as possible for each devolved administration to design policies tailored to their own needs. We are working closely with the Devolved Administrations on the design of future UK frameworks.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-06-25T13:33:29.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927899/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927899/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927899/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-06-20","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what progress has been made on the (a) design and (b) implementation of agricultural funding after 2022.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","155768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927900","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-25","<p>Current data shows that the total value of outstanding benefit overpayments for claimants living in Scotland is £278m. Of this total, £41m is for debts classified as fraud.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-06-25T11:30:57.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927900/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927900/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927900/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-20","Social Security Benefits: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the total value is of outstanding benefit (a) overpayments and (b) fraud debts owed by claimants in Scotland that are due to be recovered by her Department.","false","Biography information for Martin Whitfield","East Lothian","Martin Whitfield","155918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927901","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-28","<p>Ministers and officials are in regular contact with the Devolved Administrations. The Secretary of State last met with Ministers from the Welsh and Scottish governments and senior officials from Northern Ireland on 14 May 2018. They discussed domestic preparedness, legislative planning, frameworks and future funding.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","155771","2018-06-28T13:21:01.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927901/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927901/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927901/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-06-20","Agriculture: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many meetings he has had with the Welsh Government on the (a) design and (b) implementation of agricultural funding after 2022; and what was discussed at those meetings.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","155769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927902","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-28","<p>Ministers and officials are in regular contact with stakeholders and discuss a wide range of issues, including future funding. Details of meetings are published on the GOV.UK website, consistent with the Government’s policy on transparency and accountability.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","155772 ; 155773","2018-06-28T13:27:24.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927902/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927902/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927902/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-06-20","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will publish the minutes of the meetings he has held with the (a) National Farmers' Union Cymru and (b) Farmers' Union of Wales on the (i) design and (ii) implementation of funding schemes for agriculture after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","155770"
