"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927907","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-27","<p>Since its launch on 25 February 2018, the Combat Stress 24-hour Mental Health Helpline has received 571 calls (as of 18 Jun 2018).</p><p>Callers to the helpline are not asked at what age they joined the Armed Forces and therefore this data is not captured.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","155889","2018-06-27T15:07:43.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927907/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927907/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927907/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-20","Armed Forces: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many calls the Military Mental Health Helpline has received since it was launched.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","155888"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927908","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-27","<p>Since its launch on 25 February 2018, the Combat Stress 24-hour Mental Health Helpline has received 571 calls (as of 18 Jun 2018).</p><p>Callers to the helpline are not asked at what age they joined the Armed Forces and therefore this data is not captured.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","155888","2018-06-27T15:07:43.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927908/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927908/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927908/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-20","Armed Forces: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many calls the Military Mental Health Helpline has received from people who joined the army aged (a) 16, (b) 17, (c) 18, and (d) over 18 since that helpline was launched.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","155889"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927909","Treasury","false","2018-07-03","<p>The issues around duty free are complex, with a range of possible approaches. The government is clear that tax is a sovereign matter and that it will be open to the UK government and Parliament to decide to change its policy in the future, subject to any negotiations with the EU.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-07-03T09:07:31.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927909/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927909/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927909/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-20","Duty Free Allowances: EU Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the UK's status as a third country in December 2020 means that duty free will automatically return for UK passengers travelling to EU destinations.","false","Biography information for Sir Graham Brady","Altrincham and Sale West","Sir Graham Brady","155688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927910","Treasury","false","2018-07-03","<p>The issues around duty free are complex, with a range of possible approaches. The government is clear that tax is a sovereign matter and that it will be open to the UK government and Parliament to decide to change its policy in the future, subject to any negotiations with the EU.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-07-03T09:11:48.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927910/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927910/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927910/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-20","Duty Free Allowances: EU Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether it is his Department's policy to ensure that a return of duty free sales is available to passengers leaving the UK for the EU after December 2020.","false","Biography information for Sir Graham Brady","Altrincham and Sale West","Sir Graham Brady","155689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927911","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-06-28","<p>As the scheme is administered and funded by the BBC and not DCMS, we do not hold operational data on this scheme. However, according to the BBC Local Democracy Reporters official website, 23 contracts have been awarded to Trinity Mirror, which represents 63 journalists.</p><p>.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-06-28T15:18:57.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927911/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927911/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927911/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-06-20","Trinity Mirror","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many of the 150 journalistic posts paid for by the BBC though the local democracy reporter's service have been awarded to Trinity Mirror Group.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","East Devon","Sir Hugo Swire","155699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927912","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-25","<p>The Government is working with the Food Chain Emergency Liaison Group and additional food supply chain stakeholders to understand the impacts of the carbon dioxide shortage across the food supply chain.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-06-25T13:28:36.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927912/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927912/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927912/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-06-20","Carbon Dioxide: Shortages","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment he has made of the effect of the shortage of CO2 on (a) producers, (b) retailers, (c) customers and (d) consumers.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","155789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927913","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-25","<p>Government is aware of the CO2 shortage and industry is working to find a solution. Whilst this is an issue for industry, government will remain in contact with relevant companies and trade associations, including the British Poultry Council. We will continue to monitor the situation.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-06-25T14:14:38.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927913/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927913/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927913/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-06-20","Carbon Dioxide: Shortages","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what representations he has received from the British Poultry Council on the shortage of CO2.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","155790"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927914","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-07-04","<p>The Housing and Planning Act 2016 introduced changes to local authority tenancies by making it mandatory for most new council tenancies to be for a fixed term.</p><p>Regulations and statutory guidance are necessary to implement the fixed term tenancy provisions in the Housing and Planning Act and the next steps will be set out in due course.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-07-04T15:59:12.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927914/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927914/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927914/answer","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927914/answer/previousversion/65509","Biography information for Dominic Raab","7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-06-20","Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, when he plans to publish regulations on local Tenancy Strategies in relation to the Housing and Planning Act 2016.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","155938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927915","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-29","<p>PIP was introduced in 2013, therefore this explains the sharp increase in waiting times since 2013.</p><p>Latest figures indicate that since PIP was introduced, more than 3.1 million decisions have been made, and of these under 9% have been appealed and 4% have been overturned. For ESA the figure is only 8% of decisions made were appealed and 4% have been overturned at tribunals.</p><p> </p><p>The information requested is in the table below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="7"><p>Average time receipt to outcome (weeks)<sup> 1</sup></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p>Bradford</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>Huddersfield</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>Leeds</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr-Mar</p></td><td><p>Personal Independence Payments<sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>Employment Support Allowance<sup>3</sup></p></td><td><p>Personal Independence Payments<sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>Employment Support Allowance<sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>Personal Independence Payments<sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>Employment Support Allowance<sup>3</sup></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>28</p></td><td><p>25</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>39</p></td><td><p>26</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>22</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p>16</p></td><td><p>15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>23</p></td><td><p>22</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p>29</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>21</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>21</p></td><td><p>37</p></td><td><p>26</p></td><td><p>32</p></td><td><p>19</p></td><td><p>28</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>26</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>39</p></td><td><p>~</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>19</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>36</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>26</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>28</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>18</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>31</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>25</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>13</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>~</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><ol><li>Data include cases cleared with and without a Tribunal hearing</li><li>Personal Independent Payment (New Claim Appeals) which replaces Disability Living Allowance was introduced on the 8 April 2013, also includes Personal Independent Claims (Reassessments)</li><li>Data include Employment and Support Allowance and Incapacity Benefit reassessment. Employment and Support Allowance was introduced in October 2008 and Incapacity Benefit reassessment followed in October 2010.</li></ol><p>~ Equates to a value fewer than 5</p><p>Although care is taken when processing and analysing the data, the details are subject to inaccuracies inherent in any large-scale management system and are the best data available.</p><p>The data may differ slightly to that of the published stats as these data were run on a different date.</p><p> </p><p>The volume of PIP appeals made to the tribunal has built up over time since it was introduced as a new benefit in 2013.</p><p> </p><p>Clearance times are dependent on several factors, such as the availability of the appellant or their representative, or hearing capacity at the local Tribunal venue. Additionally, a decision on the appeal may be reached after a hearing has been adjourned (which may be directed by the judge for a variety of reasons, such as to seek further evidence), or after a hearing has been postponed (again, for a variety of reasons, often at the request of the appellant). An appeal may also have been referred back to the First-tier Tribunal by the Upper Tribunal for disposal. Cases may also have been stayed at the First-tier Tribunal, pending a decision by the Upper Tribunal on a lead case.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-06-29T13:48:34.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927915/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927915/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927915/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-20","Social Security Benefits: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the (a) current waiting time and (b) waiting time was in each year since 2010 for appeals relating to (i) personal independence payments and (ii) employment and support allowance in (A) Huddersfield, (B) Bradford and (C) Leeds.","false","Biography information for Holly Lynch","Halifax","Holly Lynch","155860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927916","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-25","<p><br>The Department publishes its workforce management transparency data on GOV.UK on a monthly basis. Data for each month in question during 2017-18 can be found at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/workforce-management" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/workforce-management</a></p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2018-06-25T16:26:53.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927916/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927916/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/927916/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-06-20","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will publish his Department's monthly workforce management data for 2017–2018.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","155721"
