"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926987","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-28","<p>Arriva Rail North has made an application under Schedule 8.3 of the franchise agreement with regards to industrial action.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-28T12:19:36.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926987/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926987/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926987/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-19","Northern: Industrial Disputes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the Answer of 15 May 2003 to Question 113237 on rail strikes, whether Arriva Northern has made an application in the last year to reimburse the company for revenues lost as a result of official industrial action.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","155260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926988","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-28","<p>Ministers have not had such discussions with Arriva Northern within the last year, but there have been discussions between officials and Arriva Rail North in the last year on this subject.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-28T12:21:37.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926988/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926988/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926988/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-19","Northern: Industrial Disputes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the Answer of 15 May 2003 to Question 113237 on rail strikes, whether he or his officials have had discussions with Arriva Northern in the last year on reimbursing Arriva Northern for revenues lost as a result of official industrial action.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","155261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926989","Home Office","false","2018-06-27","<p>The total number of releases from all Immigration Removal Centres (IRC) due to Rule 35 reports are published as part of the Migration Transparency data under the category ‘Reports made by a medical practitioner under Rule 35 by place of detention’. This can be found at the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data</a></p><p>The attached table provides a breakdown of Rule 35 releases into the sub categories of R35 (1) and R35 (3). This is provisional management information, taken from a live operational database and the numbers are subject to change.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-27T13:46:33.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926989/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926989/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926989/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-19","Immigrants: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people were released from immigration detention on the basis of Rule 35(1) and Rule 35(3) reports at each Immigration Removal Centre in (a) 2017 and (b) 2016.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","155280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/926990","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-25","<p>The Rural Payments Agency make payments under CAP within England. Payments to those who claim in Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland is a matter for the devolved administrations. A list of UK CAP beneficiaries in the last two years is available on the Defra website.</p><p>The data below is for the last full ten scheme years and provides the totals for England, and by NUTS region. Constituency level data can be found on the attached document.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Table 1. Total number of claims &gt;£500k for England</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>(a) £500k-£1m</p></td><td><p>(b) &gt;£1m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>28</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>29</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>35</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>33</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>33</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>31</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>35</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007</p></td><td><p>13</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong>Table 2. Payments by region (NUTS)</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>NUTS Regions</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2009</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2008</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2007</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>East Midland